# Documentation

- [Open Plugin](/): A standard for packaging agent extensions into distributable plugins.
- [Supported Agents](/supported-agents): Which AI coding agents support Open Plugin components.
- [Integrate Plugins Into Your Tool](/agent-builders): How to add Open Plugin support to an AI agent or development tool.
- [Getting Started](/plugin-builders): Create your first Open Plugin, test it, and distribute it.
- [Installation](/plugin-builders/installation): How plugins are installed, scoped, cached, and resolved by conformant tools.
- [Marketplace](/plugin-builders/marketplace): Grouping multiple plugins into a single distributable collection.
- [Specification](/plugin-builders/specification): The Open Plugin Specification v1.0.0 — manifest schema, directory structure, component discovery, and conformance.
- [Agents](/agent-builders/components/agents): Specialized sub-agents that a plugin provides for specific tasks.
- [Hooks](/agent-builders/components/hooks): Event handlers that respond to lifecycle events in the agent tool.
- [LSP Servers](/agent-builders/components/lsp-servers): Language Server Protocol configurations for real-time code intelligence.
- [MCP Servers](/agent-builders/components/mcp-servers): Bundle Model Context Protocol servers to provide agents with additional tools and data sources.
- [Rules](/agent-builders/components/rules): Persistent AI guidance — coding standards, best practices, and constraints.
- [Skills](/agent-builders/components/skills): Slash-command shortcuts and agent-invocable capabilities within a plugin.